          "rationale": "Texas law requires each security officer who carries a firearm on duty to hold a security officer commission from DPS, and prohibits a company from employing an armed officer who lacks one (Tex. Occ. Code 1702.161). The commission requires Level III handgun training (37 TAC 35.141) and has a term of up to two years (1702.301).",
